OL,3,CRishi Sunak criticises 'extremists'
OL,4,Cahead of on-campus antisemitism talks
OL,6,FWriting for The Times, he said: "Only
OL,7,Flast month, the UJS were themselves
OL,8,Fsubject to a shameful attempt to get
OL,9,Ftheir organisation kicked out of the
OL,10,FNUS purely because of their support
OL,11,Ffor the principle of a Jewish state."
OL,13,FHe dubbed such opposition to the UJS
OL,14,Fas the work of "extremists at the NUS".
OL,16,FMr Sunak will also host a meeting at
OL,17,FDowning Street with vice-chancellors
OL,18,Ffrom leading British universities,
OL,19,Fwith talks designed to "keep Jewish
OL,20,Fstudents safe" on campus.
